ies but also generate knowledge and reshape the cultural formation within which they emerge.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCrises in literature. 0aCrisis in literature. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aLoss (Psychology) in literaturexElectronic books. 0aLoss (Psychology) in literature. 0aMourning customs in literature. 0aPsychic trauma in literature. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aPanik. 4aTrauer. 4aTrauma. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCulture.  aMourning.  aPanic.  aTrauma.1 aAgostinho, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAgostinho, Daniela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAntz, Elisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBanki, Luisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrisley, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColla, Elisabetta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuindam, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerreira, Cátia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGanito, Tânia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonçalves, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiljković, Milan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPehkoranta, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRibeiro, António Sousa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSurmann, Frauke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTorres, Eduardo Cintra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTygstrup, Frederik, econtributor.4ct